params.account: account in which the liquidity will be calculated.
params.marketToSimulate: market in which to simulate withdraw operation.

returns.sumCollateral: sum of all collateral, already multiplied by each adjust factor (denominated in base).
returns.sumDebtPlusEffects: sum of all debt divided by adjust factor considering withdrawal (denominated in base).

assetPrice(address).details: If Chainlink's asset price is <= 0 the call is reverted.

params.priceFeed: address of Chainlink's Price Feed aggregator used to query the asset price.

returns._0: The price of the asset scaled to 18-digit decimals.

params.borrower: account in which assets are being seized.
params.repayMarket: market from where the debt will be repaid.
params.seizeMarket: market from where the assets will be seized by the liquidator.

returns.lendersAssets: amount to be added for other lenders as a compensation of bad debt clearing.
returns.seizeAssets: amount that can be seized by the liquidator.

checkBorrow(address,address).details: To be called after adding the borrowed debt to the account position.

params.borrower: address of the account that will repay the debt.
params.market: address of the market where the borrow is made.

checkLiquidation(address,address,address.details: This function can be called externally, but only will have effect when called from a market.

params.borrower: address in which the assets are being liquidated.
params.maxLiquidatorAssets: maximum amount of debt the liquidator is willing to accept.
params.repayMarket: market from where the debt is being repaid.
params.seizeMarket: market from where the liquidator will seize assets.

returns.maxRepayAssets: capped amount of debt the liquidator is allowed to repay.

checkSeize(address,address).details: This function can be called externally, but only will have effect when called from a market.

params.repayMarket: market from where the debt will be repaid.
params.seizeMarket: market where the assets will be seized.

params.account: address of the account to check for possible shortfall.
params.amount: amount that the account wants to withdraw or transfer.
params.market: address of the market where the operation will happen.

enableMarket(address,address,uint128).details: Enabling more than 256 markets will cause an overflow when casting market index to uint8.

params.adjustFactor: market's adjust factor for the underlying asset.
params.market: market to add to the protocol.
params.priceFeed: address of Chainlink's Price Feed aggregator used to query the asset price in base.

exitMarket(address).details: Sender must not have an outstanding borrow balance in the asset, or be providing necessary collateral for an outstanding borrow.

params.market: market to be disabled as collateral.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

handleBadDebt(address).details: Collateral is multiplied by price and adjust factor to be accurately evaluated as positive collateral asset.

params.account: account in which debt is being checked.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params.adjustFactor: adjust factor for the underlying asset.
params.market: address of the market to change adjust factor for.

params.priceFeed: address of Chainlink's Price Feed aggregator used to query the asset price in base.

ASSETS_THRESHOLD().notice: Maximum value the liquidator can send and still have granular control of max assets. Above this threshold, they should send `type(uint256).max`.

BASE_FEED().notice: Address that a market should have as price feed to consider as base price and avoid external price call.

TARGET_HEALTH().notice: Target health factor that the account should have after it's liquidated to prevent cascade liquidations.

accountMarkets(address).notice: Tracks the markets' indexes that an account has entered as collateral.

assetPrice(address).notice: Gets the asset price of a price feed.

calculateSeize(address,address,address,u.notice: Calculates the amount of collateral to be seized when a position is undercollateralized.

checkBorrow(address,address).notice: Validates that the current state of the position and system are valid.

checkShortfall(address,address,uint256).notice: Checks if the account has liquidity shortfall.

enterMarket(address).notice: Allows assets of a certain market to be used as collateral for borrowing other assets.

exitMarket(address).notice: Removes market from sender's account liquidity calculation.

handleBadDebt(address).notice: Checks if account has debt with no collateral, if so then call `clearBadDebt` from each market.

liquidationIncentive().notice: Liquidation incentive factors for the liquidator and the lenders of the market where the debt is repaid.

markets(address).notice: Stores market parameters per each enabled market.

priceDecimals().notice: Decimals that the answer of all price feeds should have.

setAdjustFactor(address,uint128).notice: Sets the adjust factor for a certain market.

setLiquidationIncentive((uint128,uint128.notice: Sets liquidation incentive (liquidator and lenders) for the whole ecosystem.

setPriceFeed(address,address).notice: Sets the Chainlink Price Feed Aggregator source for a market.
